# sandbox — Coding conventions

## Stack
Python 3.11+, src/ layout, uv, ruff, mypy strict, pytest.

## Code
- Type hints on every function signature
- Docstrings in numpydoc format on public API
- KISS, YAGNI, SOLID, DRY
- Single responsibility, small functions (Clean Code / Bob Martin)
- Named constants, no magic numbers
- No comments restating the code — only explain *why*

## Tests (TDD)
- Write the failing test before the implementation
- Test names describe behaviour: `test_new_creates_dated_directory`

## Commits — Conventional Commits
Format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
- Imperative mood, English, max 72 chars, no trailing period
- Types: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore, perf, ci, build

## Do not
- Add unrequested features (YAGNI)
- Refactor outside the scope of the current task
- Add defensive code for impossible cases
